HEADWORD: Semiring
<hw>Sem"i*ring`</hw> <pr>(s⟦ecr⟧m"⟦icr⟧*r⟦icr⟧ng`)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<fld>(Anat.)</fld> <def>One of the incomplete rings of the upper part of
the bronchial tubes of most birds. The semirings form an essential part
of the syrinx, or musical organ, of singing birds.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

